Here's the difference:

## `serving.yaml` — vLLM Engine Configuration

This file configures the **underlying LLM inference engine** (vLLM). It controls:

- **Model identity** — model path, HuggingFace ID, served model name, container image & digest
- **Memory & context** — `max_model_len`, `gpu_memory_utilization`, `kv_cache_dtype`, `max_num_batched_tokens`, `max_num_seqs`
- **Quantization & loading** — `quantization` (e.g. `fp8`), `load_format` (e.g. `safetensors`)
- **Attention backends** — which FlashAttention/FlashInfer backend to use
- **Sampling defaults** — `temperature`, `top_p`, `top_k`, `repetition_penalty`, `max_tokens`
- **Tool-call parser** — which parser to use (e.g. `gemma4`, `qwen3`)
- **Engine quirks** — e.g. `strip_thinking_tags`, `buffer_tool_streams`
- **Environment variables** — `VLLM_NO_USAGE_STATS`, `HF_HUB_OFFLINE`, etc.

**Key property: changing engine fields requires a vLLM restart.**

## `harness.yaml` — Agent/Conversation Configuration

This file configures the **agent layer on top of the engine**. It controls:

- **Prompts** — `system` prompt, `edit_format`, `tool_descriptions`, whether to use the system role
- **Context management** — `max_input_tokens`, compaction settings (`soft_threshold_pct`, `preserve_recent_turns`, `summarization_prompt_path`), repo map settings
- **Tool configuration** — tool format (`openai`), schema directory, grammar file, per-tool sampling overrides (e.g. `edit: { temperature: 0.0 }`), `web_fetch` allowlist, `web_search` settings
- **Agent loop** — `max_iterations`, retry budgets, self-correction behavior
- **Advanced settings whitelist** — which per-call knobs are allowed without engine restart (e.g. `reasoning_effort`, `thinking_budget`)

**Key property: these settings are hot-reloadable — no engine restart needed.**

## The relationship

A single `serving.yaml` (one loaded vLLM model) can serve multiple profile variants that differ only in their `harness.yaml` settings. The `serving.yaml` is the **heavy, restart-required** config, while `harness.yaml` is the **light, hot-reloadable** config that shapes how the model interacts with the user.
